# {{lb|nl|intransitive}} To [[be]], to [[exist]].
#: {{ux|nl|'''Zijn''' of niet '''zijn''', dat is de vraag.|t=To '''be''' or not to '''be''', that is the question.}}
#: {{ux|nl|'''Was''' je er afgelopen zaterdag ook?|t='''Were''' you there too last Saturday?}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|copular}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to connect a noun to an adjective that describes it.}}
#: {{ux|nl|De bal '''is''' rond.|t=The ball '''is''' round.}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|auxiliary}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the [[perfect tense]] of the [[active voice]] of some verbs, together with a [[past participle]].<br/>'''Note:''' The perfect tense of most other verbs is formed using [[hebben]].}}
#: {{ux|nl|Hij '''is''' hier geweest.|t=He '''has''' been here.}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|auxiliary}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the [[perfect tense]] of the [[passive voice]], together with a [[past participle]].<br/>'''Note:''' The [[imperfect tense]] passive is formed using [[worden]].}}
#: {{ux|nl|Ze '''waren''' gered.|t=They '''had been''' saved.}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur '''is''' geschilderd.|t=The wall '''has been''' painted.}}
#: {{ux|nl|De muur zal '''zijn''' geschilderd.|t=The wall will '''have been''' painted.}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|auxiliary}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to form the continuous forms of various tenses, together with '''[[aan het]]'''.}}
#: {{ux|nl|De man '''was''' aan het lopen.|t=The man '''was''' walking.}}
# {{lb|nl|intransitive}} To [[go]], to go on a [[trip]] and return.
#: {{ux|nl|Ik '''ben''' even naar de dokter.|t=I '''am going''' to the doctor for a while.}}
#: {{ux|nl|Ik ben vandaag naar het strand '''geweest.'''|t=I've '''been''' to the beach today.}}
# {{lb|nl|intransitive|impersonal}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to indicate weather, temperature or some other general condition.}}
#: {{ux|nl|Het '''is''' erg warm vandaag.|t=It '''is''' very warm today.}}
# {{lb|nl|transitive|copular|mathematics}} to [[be]], to [[equal]], to [[total]], to [[amount to]]; {{non-gloss definition|used to indicate that the values on either side of an equation are the same.}}
#: {{ux|nl|Drie keer vijf '''is''' vijftien.|t=Three times five '''is''' fifteen.}}
# {{lb|nl|intransitive}} To have the next [[turn]] in a [[game]].
#: {{ux|nl|Jij '''bent''' nu.|t=It '''is your turn''' now.}}

=====Inflection=====
Generally, the infinitive {{m|nl|wezen}}, the present participle {{m|nl|wezend}} and the present subjunctive {{m|nl|weze}} and {{m|nl|wezen}} are also used. In Belgium the singular imperative {{m|nl|zij}} is also used. While the subjunctive is considered archaic, it persists in some fixed expressions such as ''als ware'' ("as if [it] were"). 
